5 (c) Subjects a minor or vulnerable person to any of the
6 following acts, or to any substantially similar act,
7 on three or more occasions within a period of two
8 years:
9 (i) Strangling the minor or vulnerable person;
10 (ii) Biting, branding, burning, cutting, or
11 electrocuting the minor or vulnerable person;
12 (iii) Suspending the minor or vulnerable person by the
13 wrists, ankles, arms, legs, hair, or other part
14 of the body;
15 (iv) Depriving the minor or vulnerable person of
16 necessary food, water, or clothing;
17 (v) Restricting basic and necessary bodily functions
18 required for the personal hygiene of the minor or
19 vulnerable person;
20 (vi) Forcing the minor or vulnerable person to remain
21 in an area unsuitable for human habitation, such
